<dl id="jn2013e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="jn2" href="#jn2013">JN2: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/jn2all.htm#jn2013e"> (Cornell.25) 13(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> The instant of inspiration is a / spark so brief as to be invisible. / The reflection of it on many sides / at once from a multitude of / cloudy circumstances with no / one of which it is united / save by the bond of merest / possibility veils its afterglow in / an instant in a first confusion / of form. This is the instant in ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="jn2013e"><li>A Portrait <a href="../../ulex/ap/ap12d.htm#jn2013e">ED</a> </li><li><ms href="#jn2013e">MS NLI V.96-7</ms> </li><li>JJA 10:1057,9 </li><li><a name="ap5.1" href="../udra/apda.htm#ap5.1">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/ap/ap51d.htm#jn2013e">Draft: ap5.1</a></li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: See James Joyce, <cite>A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man</cite> (New York: B.W. Huebsch, 1916), <a href="https://archive.org/details/cu31924060276882/page/n261/mode/2up" target="_blank">p. 255, lines 7ff</a>.</mm> </dd></dl>
